  "prompt": "What is the healthiest food I can snack on throughout the day? Must be fairly affordable + fairly tasty.",
  "response": "When looking for a healthy, affordable, and tasty snack to enjoy throughout the day, consider the following options:\n\n1. **Fresh Fruit:** Apples, bananas, oranges, and berries are all great choices. They are packed with vitamins, fiber, and antioxidants. Plus, they are naturally sweet and satisfying.\n\n2. **Nuts and Seeds:** Almonds, walnuts, sunflower seeds, and pumpkin seeds are nutritious and provide healthy fats, protein, and fiber. Just be mindful of portion sizes, as they can be calorie-dense.\n\n3. **Greek Yogurt:** This is a great source of protein and probiotics. You can add a bit of honey or fresh fruit to enhance the flavor.\n\n4. **Vegetable Sticks:** Carrot, cucumber, bell pepper, and celery sticks are low in calories and high in vitamins. Pair them with hummus or a yogurt-based dip for added flavor.\n\n5. **Popcorn:** Air-popped popcorn is a whole grain that is low in calories and high in fiber. Avoid adding too much butter or salt to keep it healthy.\n\n6. **Whole Grain Crackers:** These can be paired with low-fat cheese or avocado for a balanced snack that includes healthy fats and fiber.\n\n7. **Hard-Boiled Eggs:** Eggs are a great source of protein and healthy fats. They are easy to prepare and can be seasoned to taste.\n\n8. **Trail Mix:** Make your own mix of nuts, seeds, and dried fruit for a customizable and nutritious snack. Be cautious with portions, as dried fruit can be high in sugar.\n\nThese options are all relatively affordable, healthy, and can be quite tasty. Remember to balance your snacks with a variety of nutrients to keep your energy levels stable throughout the day.",
